{"word":"H7033 - קָלָה - qâlâh - kaw-law' - Dried","slug":"H7033","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qâlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dried"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - qa&#x0302;la&#x0302;h</b> - <i>kaw-law'</i><p/>A primitive root (rather identical with <a href=\"#/H7034\">H7034</a> through the idea of <i>shrinkage</i> by heat); to <i>toast</i>, that is, <i>scorch</i> partially or slowly: - dried, loathsome, parch, roast."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7039\">H7039</a>"}]}